Redesign the user interface of an existing website to improve usability, visual appeal, and user experience by following a professional UX/UI design process.
Create a complete website redesign case study including the following:

## 1. Website Analysis & Heuristic Evaluation

Select an existing website and analyze its current user interface.
Perform a heuristic evaluation based on usability principles and identify:

* Navigation issues
* Poor visual hierarchy
* Accessibility problems
* Layout inconsistencies
* Confusing user interactions
* Content organization issues
* Mobile responsiveness problems

Document:

* Current website problems
* Usability issues found
* Recommended design improvements

## 2. User Research

Conduct basic user research to understand user expectations.

Include:

* Target audience identification
* User goals
* User pain points
* User behavior analysis
* Improvement opportunities

## 3. Mood Board Creation

Create a mood board that defines the visual direction of the redesigned website.

Include:

* Color palette
* Typography style
* Image style
* Design inspiration
* UI component references
* Brand personality

## 4. Style Guide Development

Create a complete UI style guide containing:

### Colors

* Primary colors
* Secondary colors
* Background colors
* Text colors

### Typography

* Heading styles
* Body text styles
* Font hierarchy

### UI Components

* Buttons
* Cards
* Navigation bars
* Forms
* Icons
* Input fields

## 5. High-Fidelity UI Mockup Design

Create detailed high-fidelity website mockups using Figma or Adobe XD.

Design the following screens:

### Desktop Version:

* Homepage
* About page
* Product/Service page
* Contact page
* User dashboard (if required)

### Mobile Version:

* Mobile homepage
* Mobile navigation menu
* Mobile content pages
* Responsive components

For each screen include:

* Layout structure
* Visual hierarchy
* UI components
* Interaction elements
* Content placement

## 6. Responsive Design

Ensure the redesigned website works properly across:

* Desktop screens
* Tablets
* Mobile devices

Apply:

* Responsive grids
* Flexible layouts
* Scalable typography
* Mobile-friendly navigation
* Optimized spacing

## 7. Design Thinking Process Documentation

Document all stages:

### Empathize

Understand user problems through research.

### Define

Create a clear problem statement based on usability issues.

### Ideate

Generate solutions to improve user experience.

### Prototype

Create high-fidelity website designs.

### Test

Gather feedback and suggest improvements.

## Expected Outcome

The final redesign should demonstrate:

* Improved visual hierarchy
* Better usability
* Effective layout design
* Modern UI principles
* Responsive web design skills
* Understanding of UX research and evaluation

Create the final output as a professional UX/UI case study suitable for a Figma portfolio, design presentation, or project submission.
